{
  "$schema": "https://modelcontextprotocol.io/schema/mcp.json",
  "description": "MCP server configuration for Themis legal framework",
  "servers": {
    "legal-research-example": {
      "url": "${LEGAL_RESEARCH_MCP_URL}",
      "api_key": "${LEGAL_RESEARCH_API_KEY}",
      "enabled": false,
      "description": "Example legal research database MCP server (configure with your provider)"
    },
    "document-repository": {
      "url": "${DOCUMENT_REPO_MCP_URL}",
      "api_key": "${DOCUMENT_REPO_API_KEY}",
      "enabled": false,
      "description": "Document management system MCP server"
    },
    "case-management": {
      "url": "${CASE_MGMT_MCP_URL}",
      "api_key": "${CASE_MGMT_API_KEY}",
      "enabled": false,
      "description": "Case management system integration (deadlines, calendar, tasks)"
    },
    "workflow-automation": {
      "url": "${WORKFLOW_MCP_URL}",
      "api_key": "${WORKFLOW_API_KEY}",
      "enabled": false,
      "description": "Workflow automation via Zapier or similar"
    }
  },
  "notes": [
    "To enable an MCP server:",
    "1. Set the environment variables for URL and API_KEY",
    "2. Change 'enabled' to true",
    "3. Restart the Themis API service",
    "",
    "Available MCP integrations:",
    "- Legal research databases (Westlaw, LexisNexis, etc.)",
    "- Document repositories (Box, SharePoint, etc.)",
    "- Case management systems (Clio, MyCase, etc.)",
    "- Workflow automation (Zapier, Make, etc.)",
    "",
    "For custom MCP servers, add a new entry with:",
    "- url: Your MCP server endpoint",
    "- api_key: Authentication token (optional)",
    "- enabled: true/false",
    "- description: What the server provides"
  ]
}
